# Project Documentation

## Project Title
Admin Dashboard with CSS Grid & Theme Switching

---

## Objective

To design and implement a responsive admin dashboard using CSS Grid layout, dynamic theme switching, and persistent theme management using localStorage.

---

## Functional Requirements

- Grid-based structured layout
- Sidebar, header, and content sections
- Dark/light mode toggle button
- Theme persistence after reload
- Responsive behavior across devices

---

## Technical Implementation

### Layout Design
- Implemented using CSS Grid
- Defined grid-template-areas for layout structure
- Responsive breakpoints for mobile compatibility

### Theme Management
- CSS variables used for color schemes
- Dark and light themes defined using :root variables
- JavaScript toggles theme class on document body

### Persistence Mechanism
- Theme preference stored using localStorage
- On page load, saved theme is retrieved and applied

Example:
```javascript
localStorage.setItem("theme", "dark");
const savedTheme = localStorage.getItem("theme");
